<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Mehndi Night Traditions</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/mehndi_traditions.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <section class="hero-mehtrad">
    <div class="hero-text-mehtrad">
      <h1> Mehndi Night Traditions</h1>
      <p class="subtext-mehtrad"><i>A Celebration of Color, Culture & Connection</i></p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container-mehtrad">
    <div class="content-mehtrad">
      <p class="center-paragraph-mehtrad">Mehndi Night, also known as Henna Night, is one of the most vibrant and emotional pre-wedding rituals celebrated in South Asian weddings. It’s more than just applying henna—this night is steeped in <strong>tradition, blessings, and joyful celebration</strong>.</p>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/mehndi-ritual.jpeg" alt="Mehndi Ritual">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad"> 
            <h2>1. The Mehndi Ritual</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• The bride’s hands and feet are adorned with intricate mehndi (henna) designs.<br> </p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • It is believed that the darker the henna, the deeper the bond between the couple.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/blessings.jpeg" alt="Blessings from Elders">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>2. Blessings from Elders</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• Elders apply a small amount of mehendi or offer blessings to the bride.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • Bride is blessed for a happy, prosperous married life and fertility.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/sangeet-dance.jpeg" alt="Sangeet and Dance">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>3. Sangeet and Dance</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• Family members and friends perform traditional songs and dances.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">• Some communities combine the Mehendi and Sangeet into one event.<br></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • It’s a way to celebrate the union of families.</div>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/hidden-name.jpeg" alt="Hidden Name Game">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>4. Hidden Name Game</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• The groom’s initials or name are hidden in the bride’s mehendi design.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • The groom is later challenged to find it—symbolizing playfulness and bonding.</div>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/haldi.jpeg" alt="Pre-Rituals">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>5. Pre-Rituals: Oil or Haldi</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• In some traditions, a bit of oil, turmeric (haldi), or sandalwood paste is applied to the bride’s skin as part of beautification and blessings.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/dress-code.jpeg" alt="Dress Code">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>6. Traditional Dress Code</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• The bride wears vibrant ethnic attire with floral jewelry.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • Guests wear bright outfits.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/folk-songs.jpeg" alt="Folk Songs & Dhol Beats">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>7. Folk Songs & Dhol Beats</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• Women of the family sing age-old folk songs specific to weddings and the bride’s journey.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad"> • This custom brings a sense of heritage and emotion to the ceremony.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="section-mehtrad">
        <div class="content-row-mehtrad">
          <div class="image-side-mehtrad">
            <img src="/img/gifts.jpeg" alt="Gifts & Tokens">
          </div>
          <div class="text-side-mehtrad">
            <h2>8. Gifts & Tokens</h2>
            <div class="image-and-points-mehtrad">
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">
            <p>• Guests often bring symbolic gifts, sweets, or jewelry.<br></p></div>
            <div class="point-box-mehtrad">• The bride may be gifted bangles, dupattas, or traditional items by her in-laws or relatives.</p></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </article>

    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
